<TITLE> DU suspends 5 BCL students for 'mugging' </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka University, Nov 03 (bdnews24.com)Dhaka University has temporarily expelled five students tied to Bangladesh Chhatra League who were caught mugging a flower trader. Proctor KM Saiful Islam Khan told bdnews24.com they had stained the university's image by being involved in mugging. "This is why they have been temporarily expelled. They cannot attend class. However, they will be able to sit exams with special permission." The proctor said, "A show-cause notice will be send to the vice chancellor regarding why they will not be permanently expelled. "The procedure for permanent expulsion will start based on his permission." The expelled are second-year Bangla student Mehrab Hossain, second-year Islamic history student Kudrat-e-Khuda and third-year year student of the same department Zaman Miah, second-year statistics student 'Zahid' and second-year philosophy student Rumman Hossain Sunny. Police arrested the six on Dhaka University campus on charges of mugging early on Saturday. Five of them are Dhaka University students and one from Dhaka College. A case was filed under the speedy tribunal act at Shahbagh Police Station. Khan said, "The arrestees had snatched money and mobile phone from a flower trader at around 4:30am." Shahbagh police chief Rezaul Karim said victim 'Rana' had filed a case against the six. Another arrestee, 'Anirban' is a student of Dhaka College. bdnews24.
